e="text" tag="optionText">They sing to attract females.</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">The females sing to attract males.</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">They are gentle animals.</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">They are easy to understand. </content></option></options><answers><answer><content type="number" tag="answerIndex">3</content></answer></answers></questionset><questionset><question><content type="text" tag="questionText">In the last paragraph, what does "heavy" mean?</content></question><options><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">great in number</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">great in weight</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">great in height</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">great in ability</content></option></options><answers><answer><content type="number" tag="answerIndex">1</content></answer></answers></questionset><questionset><question><content type="text" tag="questionText">What statement is true about humpback whales?</content></question><options><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">They make different sounds during the day.</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">They often sing very short songs.</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">They sing to attract fish.</content></option><option><content type="text" tag="optionText">The males compete for food.</content></option></options><answers><answer><content type="number" tag="answerIndex">1</content></answer></answers></questionset></questionsets></activity>